<section xml:id="dn_nova_nova" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:raxm="http://docs.rackspace.com/api/metadata" version="5.0">
    <title>Delete your network with nova-network API and nova client</title>
    <para>If you no longer need your network, you can delete it. </para>
    <para>These sections walk you through deleting your network, or virtual interface, by using the nova client.</para>
    <sidebar>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">Choose one of the following methods: </emphasis>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>If you created a network and booted a new server with that network, choose <olink
                            targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted" targetptr="nova_delete_network_nova">“Delete network (nova-network
                            API/nova)”</olink></para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>If you created a network, created a virtual interface, and attached the interface to an existing
                        server, choose <olink targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted" targetptr="nova_delete_virtual_interface_nova"
                            >“Delete virtual interface (nova-network API/nova)”</olink></para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
    </sidebar>
    <section xml:id="nova_delete_virtual_interface_nova">
        <title>Delete virtual interface (nova-network API/nova)</title>
        <procedure>
            <title>To delete a virtual interface with the nova client:</title>
            <step>
                <para>Issue the following command:</para>
                <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false">
                        <prompt>$</prompt> nova virtual-interface-delete <replaceable>instance_id</replaceable> <replaceable>interface_id</replaceable></programlisting>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Positional arguments:</emphasis></para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The ID of the server instance from which you want to detach the virtual interface.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The ID of the virtual interface that you want to delete.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Issue the following nova client command to determine if your virtual interface was deleted:
                    <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><?db-font-size 75%?>
                            <prompt>$</prompt> nova virtual-interface-list <replaceable>instance_id</replaceable></programlisting></para>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Positional argument:</emphasis></para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The ID of the server instance for which you want to list virtual interfaces. </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
                <para>After the virtual interface is deleted, it no longer appears in the list of virtual interfaces. See
                        <olink targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted" targetptr="list_virt_interfaces_for_server">“List virtual
                        interfaces for a server”</olink>.</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
        <sidebar>
            <para><emphasis role="bold">Next step: </emphasis><olink targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted" targetptr="delete_net"
                    >Delete your cloud network</olink></para>
        </sidebar>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="nova_delete_network_nova">
        <title>Delete network (nova-network API/nova)</title>
        <note><para>If you have created a virtual interface with your network, you must delete the virtual interface before
            deleting the network (see <olink targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted"
                targetptr="nova_delete_virtual_interface_nova">“Delete virtual interface (nova-network
                API/nova)”</olink>).</para></note>
        <procedure>
            <title>To delete a specified network</title>
            <step>
                <title>Delete the network</title>
                <para>Issue the following nova client command:
                    <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><?db-font-size 75%?>
                        <prompt>$</prompt> nova network-delete 29f52c7e-6efd-4335-a14a-db77d32a2555</programlisting></para>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Positional argument:</emphasis></para>
                <para>
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>The network ID of the network that you want to delete. In this example, the network ID is
                                    <literal>29f52c7e-6efd-4335-a14a-db77d32a2555</literal>. To determine the network ID,
                                issue a <command>nova</command>
                                <option>network-list</option> command.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </para>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Output:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>Successful deletion returns an <errortext>Accepted</errortext> (<returnvalue>202</returnvalue>)
                    response code:</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </section>
